END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Using [`(3,2)\text{,}`] the point-slope equation is [`y=3(x-3)+2\text{.}`] (You could use other points, like [`(2,-1)\text{,}`] and get a different-looking equation like [`y=3(x-2)+(-1)`] which simplifies to [`y=3(x-2)-1\text{.}`])

END_PGML_SOLUTION

